Mansueto Velasco.label: Mansueto Velasco
Mansueto Velasco.description: Mansueto "Onyok" Velasco, Jr. is a Filipino boxer and comedian from Bago City, Negros Occidental, Philippines. Wikipedia

Pornchai Thongburan.label: Pornchai Thongburan
Pornchai Thongburan.description: Pornchai Thongburan is a boxer from Thailand who competed in the Light Middleweight at the 2000 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal. Wikipedia

Roberto Balado.label: Roberto Balado
Roberto Balado.description: Roberto Balado Méndez was a Cuban boxer. At the 1992 Summer Olympics he won a Gold medal in the men's Super Heavyweight category. Wikipedia

Marijo Šivolija.label: Marijo Šivolija
Marijo Šivolija.description: Marijo Šivolija-Jelica is a Croatian amateur boxer best known to medal repeatedly in international competition at light heavyweight. Wikipedia

Éverton Lopes.label: Éverton Lopes
Éverton Lopes.description: Éverton dos Santos Lopes is a Brazilian amateur boxer best known to win the lightweight silver medal at the 2007 Pan American Games and for his sensational 2011 World title win. Wikipedia

Ángel Herrera Vera.label: Ángel Herrera
Ángel Herrera Vera.description: Ángel Herrera Vera is a Cuban boxer, who won two Olympic gold medals, and the world title at the second World Championships in Belgrade. Wikipedia

Aleksy Kuziemski.label: Aleksy Kuziemski
Aleksy Kuziemski.description: Aleksy Kuziemski is a Polish Light heavyweight professional boxer. Wikipedia

Adolfo Horta.label: Adolfo Horta
Adolfo Horta.description: Adolfo Horta is a retired boxer from Cuba, who won the silver medal in the Men's Featherweight division at age 22 at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow. In the final he was beaten by East Germany's Rudi Fink on points. Wikipedia

Alessio di Savino.label: Alessio di Savino
Alessio di Savino.description: Alessio di Savino is an Italian boxer who competed at the 2008 Olympics and lost his debut to Raynell Williams in the men's featherweight division. Wikipedia

Andrzej Rżany.label: Andrzej Rżany
Andrzej Rżany.description:
Andrzej Rżany is a boxer from Poland.
He participated in the 2004 Summer Olympics for his native European country. There he was stopped in the quarterfinals of the Flyweight division by Azerbaijan's eventual bronze medalist Fuad Aslanov. Wikipedia

Art Binkowski.label: Art Binkowski
Art Binkowski.description: Artur "Art" Binkowski is a Polish-born Canadian heavyweight boxer who competed for his adopted country Canada at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Australia. Wikipedia

Daniel Beahan.label: Daniel Beahan
Daniel Beahan.description: Daniel Beahan is an Australian amateur boxer best known to qualify for the Olympics 2008 at super heavyweight. He was an Australian Institute of Sport scholarship holder. Wikipedia

Fernando Atzori.label: Fernando Atzori
Fernando Atzori.description: Fernando Atzori is a former professional boxer, and olympic boxing gold medalist from Italy. Wikipedia

Henryk Średnicki.label: Henryk Średnicki
Henryk Średnicki.description: Henryk Średnicki is a retired amateur boxer from Poland, who represented his native country twice at the Summer Olympics, starting in 1976. Wikipedia

János Kajdi.label: János Kajdi
János Kajdi.description: János Kajdi was a boxer from Hungary who won the silver medal in the welterweight division at the 1972 Summer Olympics in Munich, West Germany. In the final he was defeated by Cuba's Emilio Correa on points. Wikipedia

Jesper Garnell.label: Jesper Garnell
Jesper Garnell.description: Jesper Garnell is a retired male lightweight boxer from Denmark, who represented his native country at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow, Soviet Union. Wikipedia

Kertson Manswell.label: Kertson Manswell
Kertson Manswell.description: Kertson Manswell also known as The Pride of Tobago is a heavyweight boxer from Trinidad and Tobago. Wikipedia

György Mizsei.label: György Mizsei
György Mizsei.description:
György Mizsei was a Hungarian boxer, who won a bronze medal in the light middleweight division at the 1992 Summer Olympics.
He gained the bronze medal at the 1996 European Amateur Boxing Championships in Vejle, Denmark. Wikipedia

Lars Myrberg.label: Lars Myrberg
Lars Myrberg.description:
Lars Mikael Myrberg was a Swedish boxer who won a light welterweight bronze medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics.
Myrberg turned pro in 1996 and fought only one fight, retiring with a record of 1-0-0. Wikipedia

Lorenzo Aragón.label: Lorenzo Aragón
Lorenzo Aragón.description: Lorenzo Aragón Armenteros is a Cuban boxer, who was a two-time world champion in the welterweight category. Wikipedia

Michel López Núñez.label: Michel Lopez Nuñez
Michel López Núñez.description: Michel López Núñez is a Cuban boxer who won the Super Heavyweight bronze medal at the 2004 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Michael Madsen (boxer).label: Michael Madsen
Michael Madsen (boxer).description: Michael Johannes Madsen is a retired male light-heavyweight boxer from Denmark, who represented his native country at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow, Soviet Union. Wikipedia

Nehomar Cermeño.label: Nehomar Cermeño
Nehomar Cermeño.description: Nehomar Cermeño is a professional boxer from Venezuela. He is the former interim WBA Bantamweight Champion. He is the Current interim WBA Super Bantamweight Champion. Wikipedia

Patricio Calero.label: Patricio Calero
Patricio Calero.description: Patricio Calero is a boxer from Ecuador, who represented his native country in the Men's Light Flyweight category at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece. Wikipedia

Rafael Ramos.label: Rafael Ramos
Rafael Ramos.description: Rafael “Fito” Ramos is a retired boxer from Puerto Rico. He competed in the 1984 Summer Olympics and twice won a medal at the Pan American Games during his career. Wikipedia
Rafael Ramos.Born: January 1, 1965 (age 49), Puerto Rico, United States, with Territories

Roberto Cammarelle.label: Roberto Cammarelle
Roberto Cammarelle.description: Roberto Cammarelle is an Italian boxer, best known for winning the World Amateur Boxing Championships in 2007 and 2009 as a super heavyweight and a gold medal at the 2008 Olympic Games in Beijing. Wikipedia

Patrick López.label: Patrick López
Patrick López.description: Patrick López is a light-welterweight boxer from Venezuela. He won the gold medal at the 2003 Pan American Games. Wikipedia

Satoshi Shimizu.label: Satoshi Shimizu
Satoshi Shimizu.description: Satoshi Shimizu is a boxer from Japan, who won the bronze medal in the men's bantamweight division at the 2012 Summer Olympics in London. He is Second lieutenant in the Japan Ground Self-Defense Force. Wikipedia

Stephen Sutherland.label: Stephen Sutherland
Stephen Sutherland.description:
Stephen Sutherland is an Australian amateur boxer who qualified for the 2008 Olympics at flyweight.
At the 2007 World Championships he still competed at light-flyweight where he lost to Luis Yanez. Wikipedia
Stephen Sutherland.Born: August 19, 1990 (age 23), Welwyn Garden City, United Kingdom

Tadeusz Walasek.label: Tadeusz Walasek
Tadeusz Walasek.description:
Tadeusz Walasek was a Polish boxer.
He won a silver medal for Poland at the 1960 Rome Olympic Games in the men's middleweight division. Walasek lost a 3-2 decision in the final to Eddie Crook of the United States. Wikipedia

Zsolt Bedák.label: Zsolt Bedák
Zsolt Bedák.description: Zsolt Bedák is a Hungarian boxer. His younger brother Pál Bedák is a flyweight boxer. Wikipedia

Yan Bartelemí.label: Yan Bartelemí Varela
Yan Bartelemí.description: Yan Bartelemí Varela is a Cuban amateur boxer, who won the gold medal in the light flyweight division at the 2004 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Violito Payla.label: Violito Payla
Violito Payla.description:
Violito Payla is an amateur boxer from the Philippines best known to win the Asian Games 2006 at flyweight.
At the 2002 Asian Games he beat Tulashboy Doniyorov but lost to Noman Karim. Wikipedia

Alfredo Duvergel.label: Alfredo Duvergel
Alfredo Duvergel.description: Alfredo Duvergel is a Cuban boxer. He won the silver medal in the men's light middleweight category at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta. Wikipedia

Detelin Dalakliev.label: Detelin Dalakliev
Detelin Dalakliev.description: Detelin Dalakliev is a boxer from Bulgaria. He is competing in the Bantamweight division, and won the gold medal at the World Amateur Boxing Championships in Milano 2009. Wikipedia

Ole Svendsen.label: Ole Svendsen
Ole Svendsen.description: Ole Svendsen is a retired male welterweight boxer from Denmark, who represented his native country at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow, Soviet Union. Wikipedia

Serafim Todorov.label: Serafim Todorov
Serafim Todorov.description: Serafim Simeonov Todorov is a Bulgarian former boxer who won the amateur world championship three times. He remains the last boxer to have defeated the highly regarded Floyd Mayweather, Jr. Wikipedia

Ruslan Myrsatayev.label: Ruslan Myrsatayev
Ruslan Myrsatayev.description: Ruslan Myrsatayev is a Kazakh boxer best known for qualifying in the Super Heavyweight division at the 2008 Summer Olympics. Wikipedia

Billy Ward (boxer).label: Billy Ward
Billy Ward (boxer).description: William "Billy" Ward was an Australian amateur boxer selected for the 2012 Summer Olympics in the light flyweight division. Wikipedia

Hong Moo-Won.label: Hong Moo-Won
Hong Moo-Won.description: Hong Moo-Won is a South Korean amateur boxer best known to participate at the Olympics 2004 and winning a bronze medal at the Asian Games 2006 in Doha. Wikipedia

Alexander Brand.label: Alexander Brand
Alexander Brand.description: Alexander Brand is a male boxer from Colombia, who participated in the 2003 Pan American Games for his native country, where he reached the semi-finals. Wikipedia

Diwakar Prasad.label: Diwakar Prasad
Diwakar Prasad.description: Diwakar Prasad is a male amateur boxer from India. He qualified to compete in the bantamweight division at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece, where he lost in the second round to Nigeria's Nestor Bolum. Wikipedia

Hamid Berhili.label: Hamid Berhili
Hamid Berhili.description: Hamid Berhili is a retired male boxer from Morocco, who twice competed for his North African country at the Summer Olympics 1992 and 1996. Wikipedia

Jeyhun Abiyev.label: Jeyhun Abiyev
Jeyhun Abiyev.description: Jeyhun Abiyev born October 24, 1974 in Baku is a retired male light flyweight boxer from Azerbaijan. Wikipedia

Joel Brunker.label: Joel Brunker
Joel Brunker.description: Joel Brunker is a bantamweight boxer from Australia. He competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece. He was stopped in the first round of the men's bantamweight division by bronze medalist Aghasi Mammadov. Wikipedia

Liu Yuan (boxer).label: Liu Yuan
Liu Yuan (boxer).description: Liu Yuan is a male amateur boxer from PR China. He qualified to compete at the 2004 Summer Olympics in the bantamweight division where he lost in the first round to Cuba's eventual gold medalist Guillermo Rigondeaux. Wikipedia

Lee Trautsch.label: Lee Trautsch
Lee Trautsch.description: Lee Gary Trautsch is a retired male boxer from Australia. He represented his native country at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, Georgia, where he was stopped in the first round of the men's light ... Wikipedia

Oh Kwang-Soo.label: Oh Kwang-Soo
Oh Kwang-Soo.description: Oh Kwang-Soo is a former South Korean boxer. Wikipedia

Maksym Tretyak.label: Maksym Tretyak
Maksym Tretyak.description: Maksym Volodymyrovych Tretyak is a boxer from Ukraine. Tretyak competed at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece and lost in the quarterfinals of the men's bantamweight division to bronze medalist Aghasi Mammadov. Wikipedia

Vilmos Balog.label: Vilmos Balog
Vilmos Balog.description: Vilmos Balog is a male boxer from Hungary, who competed for his native country at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece. There he was stopped in the second round of the men's welterweight division by Colombia's Juan Camilo Novoa. Wikipedia

Peter Wakefield (boxer).label: Peter Wakefield
Peter Wakefield (boxer).description: Peter Wakefield is a retired male light flyweight boxer from Australia. He competed for his native country at the 2004 Summer Olympics in Athens, Greece, where he was stopped in the second round of the ... Wikipedia

Ahmed Ismail El Shamy.label: Ahmed Ismail El Shamy
Ahmed Ismail El Shamy.description: Ahmed Ismail El Shamy is an Egyptian boxer who competed in the Men's Light Heavyweight at the 2004 Summer Olympics and won the bronze medal. Wikipedia

Aleksandr Lebziak.label: Aleksandr Lebziak
Aleksandr Lebziak.description:
Aleksandr Borisovich Lebziak is a Russian boxer, who won the Gold medal in the men's Light Heavyweight category at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney. He beat Rudolf Kraj in the final.
Lebziak also won the World Amateur Boxing Championships in 1997. Wikipedia

Gaydarbek Gaydarbekov.label: Gaydarbek Gaydarbekov
Gaydarbek Gaydarbekov.description: Gaydarbek Abdulovich Gaydarbekov is a Russian boxer who has won two Olympic medals in Middleweight. He qualified for the Athens Olympics by winning the 2004 European Amateur Boxing Championships in Pula, Croatia. Wikipedia

Alexei Lezin.label: Alexei Lezin
Alexei Lezin.description: Alexei Vladimirovich Lezin is a former Russian boxer, who won the Super Heavyweight bronze medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics. Lezin never turned pro. Wikipedia

Raimkul Malakhbekov.label: Raimkul Malakhbekov
Raimkul Malakhbekov.description: Raimkul Khudoynazarovich Malakhbekov is one of highest titled boxers of Russia, who won two Olympic medals in the Men's Bantamweight category. Wikipedia

Ramaz Paliani.label: Ramaz Paliani
Ramaz Paliani.description: Ramaz Paliani is a Georgian boxer who has won World and European Championships in the men's featherweight division. Wikipedia

Oleg Saitov.label: Oleg Saitov
Oleg Saitov.description: Oleg Elekpayevich Saitov is a Russian boxer. He studied journalism in Ryazan, a city of approximately half a million people south of Moscow. Wikipedia

Sergey Kazakov.label: Sergey Kazakov
Sergey Kazakov.description:
Sergey Kazakov is a Russian amateur boxer best known to win the World Championships 2003 and European Championships 1998, 2002 and 2004 in the Men's Light Flyweight.
Kazakov won the European Championships in 1998. Wikipedia

Abdul Rashid Qambrani.label: Abdul Rashid Qambrani
Abdul Rashid Qambrani.description: Abdul Rashid Qambrani is a retired male boxer from Pakistan, who competed for his native country at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, Georgia. Wikipedia

Art Oliver.label: Art Oliver
Art Oliver.description:
Arthur Oliver was an American boxer who competed in the 1936 Summer Olympics.
He was born in Mississippi and died at the crossing in Robertsdale, southeast of Hammond, Indiana when the truck he was riding in collided with a passenger train. Wikipedia

Andranik Hakobyan.label: Andranik Hakobyan
Andranik Hakobyan.description: Andranik Hakobyan is an Armenian amateur boxer. He is a World Cup winner, World silver medalist and two-time Olympian. Wikipedia

David Cadieux.label: David Cadieux
David Cadieux.description: David Cadieux is a professional boxer from Canada, who competed in the heavyweight division. Wikipedia

Argenis Casimiro Núñez.label: Argenis Casimiro Núñez
Argenis Casimiro Núñez.description: Argenis Casimiro Núñez is a Dominican amateur boxer best known for wining two medals at the PanAm Games. Wikipedia

Gabriel Hernández (boxer).label: Gabriel Hernández
Gabriel Hernández (boxer).description: Gabriel Hernández Romero was a male boxer from the Dominican Republic, who competed for his native country at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, Georgia. Wikipedia
Gabriel Hernández (boxer).Born: July 13, 1973 (age 40), La Romana, La Romana, Dominican Republic

Georgios Gazis.label: Georgios Gazis
Georgios Gazis.description:
Georgios Gazis is a Greek amateur boxer. He competed at the 2008 Summer Olympics in the men's middleweight division.
Gazis lost his qualifier semi to Jean-Mickaël Raymond but won the decisive third place bout against Victor Cotiujanschi. Wikipedia

Jean-Paul Mendy.label: Jean-Paul Mendy
Jean-Paul Mendy.description: Jean-Paul Mendy is a professional boxer from France, who won the bronze medal in the middleweight division at the 1997 World Amateur Boxing Championships in Budapest, Hungary. Wikipedia

Ionuţ Gheorghe.label: Ionuţ Gheorghe
Ionuţ Gheorghe.description: Ionuţ Gheorghe is a boxer from Romania. Wikipedia

Jürgen Fanghänel.label: Jürgen Fanghänel
Jürgen Fanghänel.description: Jürgen Fanghänel is a retired male boxer, who won the bronze medal for East Germany in the men's heavyweight division at the 1980 Summer Olympics in Moscow. There he was defeated in the semi finals by Piotr Zaev of the Soviet Union. Wikipedia

Károly Balzsay.label: Károly Balzsay
Károly Balzsay.description: Károly Balzsay is a Hungarian boxer and the current WBA super middleweight champion. He is also a former WBO super middleweight champion. He is nicknamed Karesz. Wikipedia

Kenneth Gould.label: Kenneth Gould
Kenneth Gould.description: Kenneth Gould was an American boxer, who won the welterweight bronze medal at the 1988 Summer Olympics. He won the world title at the 1986 World Amateur Boxing Championships in Reno, followed by a silver medal at the 1987 Pan American Games. Wikipedia

Herry Saliku Biembe.label: Herry Saliku Biembe
Herry Saliku Biembe.description: Herry Saliku Biembe is the best boxer from Democratic Republic of the Congo who qualified for the 2008 Olympics at middleweight. Wikipedia
Herry Saliku Biembe.Born: May 14, 1984 (age 29), Kinshasa, Democratic Republic of the Congo

Matvey Korobov.label: Matvey Korobov
Matvey Korobov.description: Matvey Georgiyevich Korobov is a Russian professional boxer best known for winning the middleweight amateur world title in 2005 and 2007, and being a part of the Russian team at the 2005 Boxing World Cup. Wikipedia

Nabil Kassel.label: Nabil Kassel
Nabil Kassel.description: Nabil Kassel is an Algerian boxer best known to win the middleweight gold at the 2007 All-Africa Games. The family name is Kassel, Algerians generally write this first. Wikipedia

Naim Terbunja.label: Naim Terbunja
Naim Terbunja.description:
Naim Terbunja is a Swedish amateur boxer of Kosovar-Albanian descent who qualified for the 2008 Olympics at middleweight.
Terbunja lost his round of 32 match against Matvey Korobov 18 points to 6. Wikipedia

Ramadan Yasser.label: Ramadan Yasser
Ramadan Yasser.description: Ramadan Yasser Abdel Ghaffar is a boxer from Egypt. Wikipedia

Richard Nowakowski.label: Richard Nowakowski
Richard Nowakowski.description: Richard Nowakowski is a retired boxer from East Germany, who won the silver medal in the men's featherweight division at the 1976 Summer Olympics in Montreal, Canada. There he was defeated in the final by Ángel Herrera of Cuba. Wikipedia

Richard Santiago.label: Richard Santiago
Richard Santiago.description: Richard Santiago Rodríguez is a retired male boxer from Puerto Rico, who won the bronze medal in the men's middleweight category at the 1991 Pan American Games in Havana, Cuba. Wikipedia

Paul Miller (boxer).label: Paul Miller
Paul Miller (boxer).description: Paul James Miller is a boxer from Australia, who represented his native country at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney in the Men's 75 kg Division. Wikipedia

Mohamed Hikal.label: Mohamed Hikal
Mohamed Hikal.description: Mohamed Hikal is a male boxer from Egypt. He is best known for having won a bronze medal in the men's middleweight division at the 2005 World Amateur Boxing Championships. In a remarkable career, he competed in 4 Olympic Games from 2000-2012. Wikipedia

Sherzod Abdurahmonov.label: Sherzod Abdurahmonov
Sherzod Abdurahmonov.description: Sherzod Abdurahmonov is a boxer from Uzbekistan, who participated in the 2004 Summer Olympics for his native Asian country. Wikipedia

Troy Amos-Ross.label: Troy Amos-Ross
Troy Amos-Ross.description: Troy Amos-Ross is a Guyanese Canadian boxer, currently residing in Brampton, Ontario. He competed in the light heavyweight division at the 1996 Summer Olympics in Atlanta, Georgia and 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Australia. Wikipedia

Wang Jianzheng.label: Wang Jianzheng
Wang Jianzheng.description:
Wang Jianzheng is a Chinese amateur boxer. He competed at the 2008 Olympics at middleweight.
At the World Championships, he beat three unknown fighters before running in to superstar Matvey Korobov and losing 322. Wikipedia

Gilbert Khunwane.label: Gilbert Khunwane
Gilbert Khunwane.description: Gilbert Khunwane is a male boxer from Botswana, who competed at the 2000 Summer Olympics in Sydney, Australia. There he was eliminated in the first round of the men's lightweight division by Mexico's eventual bronze medalist Cristian Bejarano. Wikipedia

Jasur Matchanov.label: Jasur Matchanov
Jasur Matchanov.description: Jasur Matchanov is an Uzbek amateur boxer from Tashkent who medaled repeatedly at 201 lbs in international tournaments. Wikipedia

Paea Wolfgramm.label: Paea Wolfgramm
Paea Wolfgramm.description: Paea Wolfgramm is a Tongan retired boxer. Nicknamed "The Tongan Warrior", Wolfgramm won the Super Heavyweight silver medal at the 1996 Summer Olympics, making him the first athlete from Tonga to win an Olympic medal. Wikipedia

Santiago Lovell.label: Santiago Lovell
Santiago Lovell.description: Alberto Santiago Lovell, known as Alberto Lovell, was a boxer Argentine heavyweight, who won the gold medal in the Olympic Games in Los Angeles 1932. Wikipedia

Wilhelm Gratschow.label: Wilhelm Gratschow
Wilhelm Gratschow.description: Wilhelm Gratschow is a German amateur boxer who qualified for the 2008 Olympics. Wikipedia

Guillermo Lovell.label: Guillermo Lovell
Guillermo Lovell.description: Guillermo José Lovell was a boxer Argentine heavyweight, who won the silver medal in the 1936 Berlin Olympics. Wikipedia
